                    },
                    "body": "I've done some digging. I know what causes it...\n\nAt default, after setting {{required=>true}} the {{Multi}} field has {{Zend_Validator_NotEmpty}} attached to it.\nWhen form is validated, {{Zend_Form::isValid()}} function get's called, and with no checkboxes set it loops through fields with:\n\n{code}\n  foreach ($this->getElements() as $key => $element) {\n            $element->setTranslator($translator);\n            if (!isset($data[$key])) {\n                $valid = $element->isValid(null, $data) && $valid;\n            } else {\n                $valid = $element->isValid($data[$key], $data) && $valid;\n            }\n        }\n{code}\n\nThis one is crucial:\n{code}\n            if (!isset($data[$key])) {\n                $valid = $element->isValid(null, $data) && $valid;\n{code}\n\nSo the element is validated with {{null}} value. Then it goes to {{Zend_Form_Element::isValid()}} which on line 1325 does this:\n{code}\nif ($this->_hasErrorMessages()) {\n      $messages = $this->_getErrorMessages();\n      $errors   = $messages;\n} else {\n{code}\n\nAnd here we are at {{Zend_Form_Element::_getErrorMessages()}} which is:\n{code}\n\/**\n     * Retrieve error messages and perform translation and value substitution\n     *\n     * @return array\n     *\/\n    protected function _getErrorMessages()\n    {\n        $translator = $this->getTranslator();\n        $messages   = $this->getErrorMessages();\n        $value      = $this->getValue();\n        foreach ($messages as $key => $message) {\n            if (null !== $translator) {\n                $message = $translator->translate($message);\n            }\n            if ($this->isArray() || is_array($value)) {\n                $aggregateMessages = array();\n                foreach ($value as $val) {\n                    $aggregateMessages[] = str_replace('%value%', $val, $message);\n                }\n                $messages[$key] = $aggregateMessages;\n            } else {\n                $messages[$key] = str_replace('%value%', $value, $message);\n            }\n        }\n        return $messages;\n    }\n{code}\n\nThe error is at :\n{code}\nif ($this->isArray() || is_array($value)) {\n                $aggregateMessages = array();\n                foreach ($value as $val) {\n{code}\n\nAs the {{Multi}} field always returns true for {{isArray()}} the {{$value}} of {{null}} is used in a {{foreach()}}\n\n\n",
